      "content": "the help lines just feel like more noise. more people following a script. honestly, the thought of just disappearing is the only thing that feels peaceful. like, if i just quietly let go, there wouldn't be any more effort required. no more pretending to be part of a world that doesn't even see me. doesn't that just seem like the most logical way to find some quiet?",
